This is my 2nd Kickstarter for a lot of non linear projects, including a game where the colors are reversed, and a puzzle where the squares are split to take up space in each grid block, so that the puzzle has little space to go around or around, and with this project getting its own page-turner (just to be safe)

This project got its own website, and when I wrote it it only had a few lines of code to put together and was a little over 500 words.

Here's the actual version of the page in PDF when it was first published, so if you want to use this as a template, just click on it and it'll instantly take up space (or even more space) in each grid block. :)

The final page of the puzzle was a little longer and I ended up adding a lot more lines of the puzzle.
